00:27:39.800 --> 00:27:43.670
Maximizing profits-- now that
we defined what profits are,

00:27:43.670 --> 00:27:45.920
how do you maximize them?

00:27:45.920 --> 00:27:48.020
We know how to
maximize a function.

00:27:48.020 --> 00:27:54.073
If pi equals R minus C,
then the maximum d pi dq--

00:27:54.073 --> 00:27:55.240
you can't control the price.

00:27:55.240 --> 00:27:57.650
All you can control is
how much you produce.

00:27:57.650 --> 00:28:00.890
Your only control
variable is q, little q.

00:28:00.890 --> 00:28:08.670
So d pi dq equals dR d
little q minus dC d little q.

00:28:08.670 --> 00:28:09.957
Know what dC d little q is.

00:28:09.957 --> 00:28:11.040
We defined that last time.

00:28:11.040 --> 00:28:13.660
What's that?

00:28:13.660 --> 00:28:16.790
What do we call that, the
change in costs with respect

00:28:16.790 --> 00:28:18.720
to an increment in quantity?

00:28:18.720 --> 00:28:19.720
AUDIENCE: Marginal cost.

00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:21.012
JONATHAN GRUBER: Marginal cost.

00:28:21.012 --> 00:28:23.960
So we know this is
the marginal cost,

00:28:23.960 --> 00:28:29.690
but for a competitive firm,
what is marginal revenue?

00:28:29.690 --> 00:28:31.490
So that's marginal
revenue, the amount you

00:28:31.490 --> 00:28:33.860
work on the next unit you sell.

00:28:33.860 --> 00:28:38.830
For a competitive firm, what
is their marginal revenue?

00:28:38.830 --> 00:28:40.193
What is the amount?

00:28:40.193 --> 00:28:40.860
AUDIENCE: Price.

00:28:40.860 --> 00:28:42.818
JONATHAN GRUBER: Price,
which is given to them,

00:28:42.818 --> 00:28:45.720
because they're a price taker.

00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:48.178
Firms, they don't have to think
about a complicated concept

00:28:48.178 --> 00:28:48.678
here.

00:28:48.678 --> 00:28:50.530
This is all complicated,
with tons of math.

00:28:50.530 --> 00:28:52.570
I hated that last
