00:46:25.520 --> 00:46:29.540
So basically, suppose the price
in this market fell to $10.

00:46:32.650 --> 00:46:37.210
Should you continue to
participate in the market?

00:46:37.210 --> 00:46:41.190
Well, if the price
falls to $10, what

00:46:41.190 --> 00:46:43.784
is the optimal
level of production?

00:46:43.784 --> 00:46:44.730
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:46:44.730 --> 00:46:46.400
JONATHAN GRUBER: Zero.

00:46:46.400 --> 00:46:51.280
So does that mean
you should walk away?

00:46:51.280 --> 00:46:52.480
No.

00:46:52.480 --> 00:46:53.710
What are your profits?

00:46:53.710 --> 00:46:58.410
If you sell zero,
what are your profits?

00:47:01.370 --> 00:47:02.270
Negative 10.

00:47:02.270 --> 00:47:06.950
If you shut down and walk
